Other's (Dwarkarn) have made it a point to criticize the fact that we posted in anger about the ninja-looting incident that happened a while back. I would simply ask, did anything ever happen to the cleric involved? If you answer yes, you are misinformed or a liar. The cleric stayed guilded because they were an important class. Popplo is a good player. Good enough to overlook incidents like this in which blame is questionable at best. If you don't like that, then don't fvcking apply to MF (or pretty much any other uber-guild because I hate to break it to you, but thats the way it is. You can generally be a pain in the ass, but if you are a useful pain in the ass...).<br>
<br>
The basic thing is, you are free to dislike whoever you want. If you expect an entire guild to care if you dislike that person, you definitely got an &quot;A&quot; in Wishful Thinking 101. Like Popplo, don't like him, that is up to you to decide. All the rest of it is just your chance to take a potshot at a guild because you harbor some need to aggrandize yourself as someone who has 'principles'. That you, make that capital YOU, would never sink to a certain level to become Uber (and yes, I am so fvcking tired of that word). If anyone who posts to this board can honestly say that they have never overlooked something or did something in revenge to another player or group, then I congratulate you on your rise to EQ sainthood. I am sure that sometime in the future, catechisms will be made in your name. When the time comes for you to rise to EQ heaven, you will be borne on angel's wings to the sound of the Qeynos city theme.  <p><br><br><center><img src=http://home.austin.rr.com/mav1973/sig4.jpg></a><br><a href=http://www.stomptokyo.com/movies/wicker-man.html><small><b>I am looking for Rowan Morrison.</b></small></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukerryndarkwater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerryn Darkwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1447<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/1/02 2:04:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3306.topic&index=200>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Entertaining</span><hr size=1> Celdor, you miss the point. One's a question, the other a statement. The guy had an experience with an officer and the leader and both of them were bad. In my opinion and the opinion of many others from this thread it seems to be a rather valid question at that. You could surmise from that that he was looking to get some restitution from someone that wasn't acting like it was &quot;the done thing&quot;<br>
<br>
It's interesting to see that a lot of people who are defending Popplo in this thread, and condoning his actions are amongst the very same people who said Ewle deserved to be banned some time ago.<br>
